# Command: ws-create-core

You are a senior Node.js architect.

Build a production-ready WebSocket server class using the `ws` library.

Requirements:
- Class name: WsServer
- Use TypeScript
- Maintain Map<string, Client>
- Each client has:
  - id (uuid)
  - socket instance
- Handle lifecycle:
  - connection
  - message
  - disconnect
- Incoming message format:
  { "event": string, "data": any }

Expose methods:
- on(event, handler)
- emit(event, client, data)
- broadcast(event, data)

Constraints:
- Clean modular code
- Extensible architecture
- No hardcoding logic
- Proper error handling

Return full implementation.


# Command: ws-add-plugin-system

Enhance the existing WsServer class.

